FlySafair was the country’s most punctual airline in 2018, taking off from the main three airports on time at least nine times out of 10. The on-time measure is calculated by Airports Company SA (Acsa). Acsa’s website states that it uses the “International Airlines Transport Association (Iata) universal standard benchmark, which considers a 15-minute deviation from the scheduled time as an on-time departure”.
From January to November 2018, the FlySafair statistics were: FlySafair departed from Durban’s King Shaka Airport on time for 94.80% of its flights;
At Cape Town’s International Airport, it scored 92.71%;
At OR Tambo Airport in Johannesburg, the four-year-old airline left punctually 93.49% of the time. In contrast, Kulula.com flights missed the 85% target on-time target set in partnership with Acsa at all three big airports this year.
